                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 365.117/459</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Ambassador <persName type="from">Page</persName> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Rome</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-11-17">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 17, 1916</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>733. Department’s 324, April 18. Military authorities hold that, while Orocchi
                    may have lost Italian citizenship during minority <pb facs="0504" n="428"
                        xml:id="pg_428"/> owing to naturalization his father, nevertheless, this
                    fact does not exempt him from military obligations towards Kingdom according
                    terms Article 12, Civil Code, held to be applicable in his case.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Nelson Page</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
